<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN374-intro">
    <p type="edition">tiṇai, pāṭāṇṭiṇai. tuṟai, pūvainilai. āy aṇṭiraṉai uṟaiyūr ēṇiccēri muṭamōciyār.
    </p>
    <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
    </p>
  </div>
    <div xml:id="PN374">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kāṉaṉ mēyntu viyaṉpulat talkum</l>
<l>pulvā yiralai neṟṟi yaṉṉa</l>
<l>polamilaṅku ceṉṉiya pāṟumayir viyarppat</l>
<l>taṇpaṉi yuṟaikkum pularā ñāṅkar</l>
<l>maṉṟap palaviṉ mālvarai poruntiyeṉ</l>
<l>ṟeṇkaṇ mākkiṇai teḷirppa voṟṟi</l>
<l>yiruṅkalai yōrppa vicaiik kāṇvarak</l>
<l>karuṅkōṟ kuṟiñci yaṭukkam pāṭap</l>
<l>pulippaṟ ṟālip puṉṟalaic ciṟāar</l>
<l>māṉkaṇ makaḷirk kāṉṟē rakaṉṟuvā</l>
<l>cilaippāṟ paṭṭa muḷavumāṉ koḻuṅkuṟai</l>
<l>viṭarmukai yaṭukkattuc ciṉaimutir cāntap</l>
<l>pukarmuka vēḻattu maruppoṭu mūṉṟu</l>
<l>miruṅkēḻ vayappuli variyataṭ kuvaii</l>
<l>viruntiṟai nalku nāṭa ṉeṅkōṉ</l>
<l>kaḻaṟoṭi yāa yaṇṭiraṉ pōla</l>
<l>vaṇmaiyu muṭaiyaiyō ñāyiṟu</l>
<l>koṉviḷaṅ kutiyāl vicumpi ṉāṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="8d">As, </l>
<l corresp="3">so that the dishevelled hair one [my] golden shining head perspires </l>
<l corresp="2">like the forehead of the Iralai deer </l>
<l corresp="1">that grazes in the seashore grove [and] stays in the wide fields, </l>
<l corresp="4">at the time that does not become dry when cool dew drips, </l>
<l corresp="5">I join the big mountain with a jackfruit tree in a village common, </l>
<l corresp="6">beat my clear-eyed Kiṇai drum so that it sounds, </l>
<l corresp="7">sounding [it] while a dark stag/monkey listens, [and] visibly </l>
<l corresp="8">sing by the slope with black-stalked Kuṟiñci, </l>
<l>resembling Āay Aṇṭiraṉ with anklets [and] bracelets, (16),</l>
<l corresp="15">our king, man from a land, where grants a seat at [his] feast/to guests </l>
<l corresp="10">[even] the young man, after having departed to search the forest, with doe-eyed women </l>
<l corresp="9">[and] ruddy-haired children with tiger-tooth Tālis, </l>
<l corresp="14">[and] heaped on the striped skin of a dark, lustrous, strong tiger </l>
<l corresp="13">three things, [namely] with the tusk of an elephant bull with spotted face </l>
<l corresp="12">mature sandal from the branches in the mountain side with clefts [and] caves, </l>
<l corresp="11">[and] fat pieces of a male porcupine that fell to the bow, </l>
<l corresp="17">– do you also possess munificence, sun? </l>
<l corresp="18">You would vainly shine in the sky. </l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="9-16">
<l>resembling Āay Aṇṭiraṉ with anklets [and] bracelets, (16),</l>
<l corresp="15">our king, man from a land, who grants a seat at [his] feast/to guests </l>
<l corresp="14">after heaping on the striped skin of a dark, lustrous, strong tiger </l>
<l corresp="13">three things, [namely] with the tusk of an elephant bull with spotted face </l>
<l corresp="12">mature sandal from the branches in the mountain side with clefts [and] caves, </l>
<l corresp="11">[and] fat pieces of a male porcupine that fell to the bow, </l>
<l corresp="9">when ruddy-haired youngsters with tiger-tooth Tālis </l>
<l corresp="10">had departed to search the forest for the sake of doe-eyed women [and] come back, </l>
</lg>
</lg>
